Summary: A star shape that looked like it was being moved around by our strong winds
trends: There have been 3 other sightings in Lowestoft
There were no other sightings in Lowestoft on or around March 12th 2008
divs: Sighting DetailsAt 9pm I let my dog out into the garden, whilst waiting for him I was looking around at sky over the north sea & noticed a star that looked as though it was being moved around by the strong winds. It was going up & down & side to side. I then called my husband out & he saw the same thing. I also saw this star last sept. What is it? Iknow our winds cant affect stars. I couldnt sleep thinking about it & got up at 4am & it was still there.
